00:36:40.530 --> 00:36:41.530
[laughter]

00:36:41.530 --> 00:36:44.170
&gt;&gt;Jeff: I figure that was a compliment.

00:36:44.170 --> 00:36:49.610
&gt;&gt;Nathan: Yes, exactly. I figured that was
a good thing. So then, I was also always interested

00:36:49.610 --> 00:36:56.220
in technology and science. I never became
a chef professionally. And there's probably

00:36:56.220 --> 00:37:01.260
a parallel universe where I did, but instead,
I became a physicist, actually.

00:37:01.260 --> 00:37:06.800
I got a PhD in Physics. I worked for Stephen
Hawking, but then took a leave of absence

00:37:06.800 --> 00:37:10.950
for a summer to work on a software project.
And we started a company. And then after a

00:37:10.950 --> 00:37:15.099
couple years, Microsoft bought the company
and whatever. So then, finally when I retired

00:37:15.099 --> 00:37:18.790
from Microsoft, I started cooking a lot more.
I had a lot more time to cook.

00:37:18.790 --> 00:37:22.210
And that's where I really started getting
into all of the real cutting-edge techniques.

00:37:22.210 --> 00:37:30.000
Well, what's the highest technology cooking
