00:44:05.490 --> 00:44:08.440
book and figuring out what we do next.

00:44:08.440 --> 00:44:14.220
&gt;&gt;Male Audience Member #5: Hi. Thanks for
a great talk. I noticed that your tag line

00:44:14.220 --> 00:44:19.990
is "a revolution in the art of cooking," and
I think it's patently obvious to everyone

00:44:19.990 --> 00:44:24.180
that you've really advanced to science of
cooking in bringing all this together. How

00:44:24.180 --> 00:44:28.050
does it change the art? Obviously there's
some art in these pictures. But what do you

00:44:28.050 --> 00:44:29.050
think about that?

00:44:29.050 --> 00:44:36.980
&gt;&gt;Nathan: OK. Well, there's two answers to
that. The first is engineering underlies art.

00:44:36.980 --> 00:44:42.060
There are a bunch of masterpieces that Leonardo
da Vinci created that are lost because he

00:44:42.060 --> 00:44:47.170
tried a brand new technique for the paint
and the damn paint fell off the wall.

00:44:47.170 --> 00:44:53.270
So, empowering chefs by giving them new techniques--and
there's the kitchen again--it's in a space

00:44:53.270 --> 00:45:00.609
that used to be a Harley-Davidson dealership
and service center. And then they moved. And

00:45:00.609 --> 00:45:05.109
we still get these guys that look like they
came out of a ZZ Top video coming up and saying,

00:45:05.109 --> 00:45:08.849
"Well, where do I get my Hog serviced?" I
say, "Well, they moved down the street."

00:45:08.849 --> 00:45:14.010
So, we took it and turned it into this. To
answer your question, the rest of your question,

00:45:14.010 --> 00:45:21.020
part of the art comes in enabling art through
science and engineering. Part of it is we

00:45:21.020 --> 00:45:26.070
take a lot of effort in the book to discuss
cooking as art. And one of the reasons we

00:45:26.070 --> 00:45:31.880
call it "Modernist Cuisine" is we draw a lot
of parallels between modernism, which was

00:45:31.880 --> 00:45:40.310
this idea that changed art and architecture
and literature, philosophy in the 19th and

00:45:40.310 --> 00:45:41.550
the 20th centuries.

00:45:41.550 --> 00:45:47.560
Cooking never got its modernist period, I
argue, until now. And so, we think that in

00:45:47.560 --> 00:45:54.870
fact, this is about art. And I'd love to point
out that cooking is an art. Art is about engaging

00:45:54.870 --> 00:46:01.671
us through our emotions. And the analogy I
like best is actually to architecture because

00:46:01.671 --> 00:46:06.280
architecture is necessary. Painting and sculpture
are not quite as necessary, but you need a

00:46:06.280 --> 00:46:07.670
roof over your head.

00:46:07.670 --> 00:46:13.810
And so, most buildings in the world are pretty
dull. They're warehouses and they're truly

00:46:13.810 --> 00:46:19.380
dull buildings, but they're necessary. Most
meals in the world are the same way. They're

00:46:19.380 --> 00:46:26.530
not art. They're necessary because we need
food as fuel for our bodies. But in both food

00:46:26.530 --> 00:46:32.859
and architecture, you can create amazing artistic
things that grab your emotions and thrill

00:46:32.859 --> 00:46:35.270
people in a way like nothing else can. So.

00:46:35.270 --> 00:46:37.780
&gt;&gt;Male Audience Member #5: Thanks.

00:46:37.780 --> 00:46:43.700
&gt;&gt;Male Audience Member #6: I was curious if
you went off at all on the tangent of nutrition,

00:46:43.700 --> 00:46:44.700
so that you can talk a little bit about--

