&gt;&gt;Nathan: Oh, we went off on so many tangents
in this book it's ridiculous. So, one of the

00:46:51.010 --> 00:46:58.960
things--. That's sea urchin on cocoa noodles.
So in our thing on heat and energy, everybody

00:46:58.960 --> 00:47:05.369
knows that their various electrical appliances
draw watts. Well we put a little biography

00:47:05.369 --> 00:47:10.030
of James Watt in to explain why those things
are called watts.

00:47:10.030 --> 00:47:15.490
We have a whole chapter called "Food and Health,"
which covers nutrition, sort of. I don't mean

00:47:15.490 --> 00:47:20.660
we comprehensively cover nutrition. But we
decided to tackle a very controversial issue,

00:47:20.660 --> 00:47:24.460
which is what food is good for you and what
food is not good for you. Because there's

00:47:24.460 --> 00:47:29.180
a tremendous amount of popular information
